# Security invariants (template)

Canonical detail: root `AGENTS.md`, `docs/guides/auth-invariants.md`, `docs/guides/web-security-baseline.md`, `docs/architecture/database.md`.

## Machine-checkable (run before merge)

- `pnpm check:forbidden` — no server `getSession()` for authz, no `createAdminClient` outside `@workspace/supabase-data` + infra client file, no app-local `lib/db`, no hand-edited `database.types.ts`, stamped migrations only, no `packages/ui` edits without allowlist.
- `pnpm check:security-smells` — no unsafe `NEXT_PUBLIC_*SECRET*` / `*SERVICE_ROLE*` / `*PRIVATE_KEY*` names; no `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in `use client` modules; `.env.example` must not assign a value to `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`.

## Auth and abuse

- Server authorization: `getClaims()` (not `getSession()`). Session refresh: root `apps/<app>/proxy.ts` + `@workspace/supabase-auth/proxy/update-session`.
- Sensitive auth routes: call `protectSensitiveAuthRoute` before GoTrue / token work. In **`NODE_ENV=production`**, set `AUTH_RATE_LIMIT_MODE=memory` (single-instance / previews) or wire a durable limiter — default is **fail closed (503)** until configured.

## Data and secrets

- Data access lives in `@workspace/supabase-infra` (clients/env/types) and `@workspace/supabase-data` (actions/repos). No `apps/*/lib/db` or app-local repositories.
- Regenerate `database.types.ts` only via `pnpm supabase:types:local` or `pnpm supabase:types:linked`; merge fixes in `database.ts`.
- Migrations: `pnpm supabase:migration:new -- <name>` only; never hand-create SQL under `supabase/migrations/`.

## Browser and transport

- Security headers for Next apps: copy `apps/example/lib/security-headers.mjs` + `next.config.mjs` pattern. Opt-in enforcing CSP: root `CSP_ENFORCE=1` (see `docs/guides/web-security-baseline.md`).
- HSTS at the **CDN / edge**, not blindly in Next config.

## DB changes

- Any RLS / migration / RPC / authz-sensitive SQL change: run **`pnpm test:db`** locally before claiming merge-ready.
